                                      <div class="c-Accrd__header-title">
                                          <span>Mridangam</span>
                                          <span>Sri. Balu Rajendrakurup</span>
                                      </div>
                                  </div>
                              </header>
                              <div class="c-Accrd__cnt">
                                  <p>BaluKurup is a renowned Mridangist & percussionist who experiments with multiple genres like Indian Classical, Jazz, African and world music percussion. He is fortunate to be a small leaf of huge Banyan tree, TheThanjavurBani Mridangam lineage of Palghat Mani Iyer,under renowned gurus Sri.Nagoor AmbiIyer, Sri Mavelikara Velukutty Nair and Sri.Erickavu Sunil. Balu has been performing for notable maestros in south Indian film music fraternity and carnatic music exponents for the last 25 years. He is part of Valle Venia, a symphony group based in Germany and performs for world music concerts across European countries, US and the Middle East.Balu believes music is a universal medium to communicate the most innate expressions with nature and is open to experimenting with any form of music and artists.</p>
                              </div>
                          </article>
